{"questionId":"9076717","questionHtml":"<p>Monochromatic light from a single source is incident on two thin, parallel slits.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4856/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-14_om_07.10.48.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/HP2/ENG/TZ2/05.b_01\"></p>\n<p>The following data are available.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage mjpage__block\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\" alttext=\"\\begin{array}{*{20}{l}} {{\\text{Slit separation}}}&amp;{ = 0.12{\\text{ mm}}} \\\\ {{\\text{Wavelength}}}&amp;{ = 680{\\text{ nm}}} \\\\ {{\\text{Distance to screen}}}&amp;{ = 3.5{\\text{ m}}} \\end{array}\">\n  <mtable columnalign=\"left\" rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Slit separation</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>0.12</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;mm</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Wavelength</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>680</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;nm</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Distance to screen</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>3.5</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;m</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n  </mtable>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>The intensity <em>I </em>of light at the screen from each slit separately is <em>I</em><sub>0</sub>. Sketch, on the&nbsp;axes, a graph to show the variation with distance <em>x </em>on the screen of the intensity of light&nbsp;on the screen for this arrangement.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/58e379f20f906958c6b0102fcddae504c2916307.png\"></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>«</strong>standard two slit pattern<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>general shape with a maximum at <em>x </em>= 0</p>\n<p>maxima at 4<em>I</em><sub>0</sub></p>\n<p>maxima separated by&nbsp;<strong>«</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{D\\lambda }}{s}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>D</mi>\n      <mi>λ</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>s</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =<strong>»</strong>&nbsp;2.0 cm</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept single slit modulated pattern provided central maximum is at 4. ie height of peaks decrease as they go away from central maximum. Peaks must be of the same width</em></p>\n<p><em><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4858/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-14_om_07.15.48.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/HP2/ENG/TZ2/05.b/M\"></em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[3 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076717","referenceCode":"18M.2.HL.TZ2.b","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Monochromatic light from a single source is incident on two thin, parallel slits. The following data are available. Slit separation = 0.12 mm Wavelength = 680 nm Distance to screen","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena","9.3 – Interference","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}